{
  "texts": [
    "Second, we showed that GPT-4 used more complex words than humans, but complexity was only weakly associated with quality.",
    "Finally, we showed that humans and GPT-4 use unique words that can be used to predict the source of reappraisal.",
    "We also show that when humans use these words, which appear to be more complex, their reappraisals are rated as higher quality.",
    "This last finding can be interpreted as both showing that what differentiates humans and GPT-4 is the use of a certain vocabulary, or that inherent ability is a corollary of these terms.",
    "Our findings carry significant implications for the application of AI in reappraisal and broadly in the support of mental health."
  ]
}